over the previous way of doing things, which is, like, you adjust stuff in your Cordo document,

00:10:53.940 --> 00:10:57.619
and then you have to also do it in your Shiny app, but in a different way, and then things

00:10:57.619 --> 00:11:00.340
look sort of different.

00:11:00.340 --> 00:11:06.619
So yeah, I think it's, like, and then on the developer relations team, like, we're trying

00:11:06.619 --> 00:11:14.659
to develop a team-wide style, and I think for that use case, like, brand.yaml is really

00:11:14.659 --> 00:11:15.659
great.

00:11:15.659 --> 00:11:16.659
Awesome.

00:11:17.380 --> 00:11:19.380
Yeah, I'm not sure about surprising, but.

00:11:19.380 --> 00:11:21.380
Well, yeah, but no, that was perfect.

00:11:21.380 --> 00:11:22.380
Thank you.

