00:26:07.300 --> 00:26:15.300
brandy ammo and turn it into your theme in the CSS for your theme in Shiny or in our

00:26:15.300 --> 00:26:22.579
ecosystem, we take key parts of it and create convenient little SAS variables for you.

00:26:22.579 --> 00:26:25.540
Actually, we create SAS and CSS variables for you.

00:26:26.099 --> 00:26:35.459
So, for example, if you define a custom color, so you define your custom red under color

00:26:35.459 --> 00:26:36.339
dot palette, right?

00:26:36.339 --> 00:26:40.420
So, under the color palette, you put your own red color.

00:26:40.420 --> 00:26:47.459
We'll actually create a SAS variable that is dollar brand dash red, which means that

00:26:47.459 --> 00:26:51.780
you can then access that anywhere you want in your SAS files.

00:26:52.339 --> 00:27:02.260
And, yeah, beyond that, I think this starts to get pretty specific in terms of exactly

00:27:02.260 --> 00:27:08.739
how you layer your theme that includes brand with extra rules and things like that.

00:27:09.859 --> 00:27:13.619
In which case, it is much easier to see like an actual concrete example.

00:27:13.619 --> 00:27:19.699
And I am very happy to answer any questions in the about this, either in the BS lib repo

00:27:19.780 --> 00:27:26.739
or just by going to the brandy ammo website and clicking on report an issue.

