00:27:53.219 --> 00:27:57.859
So, before we get to this question, Jeff asked the question about my Shiny apps tend to make

00:27:57.859 --> 00:28:01.780
heavy use of HTML widgets like Plotly, Leaflet, DT, et cetera.

00:28:02.979 --> 00:28:03.380
Thank you.

00:28:04.900 --> 00:28:10.099
The answer is, unfortunately, these libraries need to be sort of like they need to learn

00:28:10.099 --> 00:28:15.540
to speak brand YAML in the same way that we taught Quarto and Shiny to speak brand YAML.

00:28:15.540 --> 00:28:20.900
So, support for these will come sort of gradually over time as people make pull requests into

00:28:20.900 --> 00:28:25.219
these open source libraries to add support for brand YAML in the same way that you would

00:28:26.020 --> 00:28:28.660
do like we did for Quarto and for Shiny.

00:28:28.660 --> 00:28:30.099
We just added that feature.

00:28:30.099 --> 00:28:31.699
So, that doesn't happen automatically.

00:28:31.699 --> 00:28:32.819
That will happen over time.

00:28:33.540 --> 00:28:37.060
But that's the point of doing brand YAML is that it enables this kind of work.

00:28:37.060 --> 00:28:38.979
So, now the configuration happens in one place.

00:28:38.979 --> 00:28:43.540
And so, we expect this to become progressively better as time goes by.

00:28:43.699 --> 00:28:44.260
Yeah.

00:28:44.260 --> 00:28:50.660
And, again, brand YAML stands on the shoulders of a lot of work that has been done in the past.

00:28:51.380 --> 00:28:56.020
In particular, I'd like to call out Carson Sievert's work on getting theming to work

00:28:56.020 --> 00:28:58.819
in general in Shiny through BSLib.

00:28:58.819 --> 00:29:03.859
So, there is a good chance that a lot of these widgets, when they're in a Shiny app that

00:29:03.859 --> 00:29:11.219
is themed matching brand YAML, will just pick up important theming properties from the main

00:29:11.219 --> 00:29:11.780
Shiny app.

00:29:11.859 --> 00:29:16.420
And if they don't, that's something that we would be interested in taking a look at.

