00:32:39.060 --> 00:32:43.540
And so, we haven't implemented that, but it's sort of on the roadmap.

00:32:43.540 --> 00:32:51.699
It's figuring out how to make the brand YAML configuration kick in for the email format.

00:32:52.420 --> 00:32:56.579
The reason this is not just HTML is that email is a much more restrictive format on what

00:32:56.579 --> 00:32:59.219
it allows to do in terms of CSS, in terms of styling.

